                  ADDITIONAL TERMS UNDER AGPLv3 SECTION 7
================================================================================

Pursuant to Section 7 of the GNU Affero General Public License v3.0, the
following additional non-permissive terms apply to this software. These terms
form part of the license. Any party redistributing or running this software
agrees to honor them.

This software is offered to the world as a tool for collective practice by the
dispossessed. It is not a neutral instrument. The following uses are NOT
authorized, and any such use is a violation of this license that automatically
terminates the licensee's rights under AGPLv3 (per Section 8):

  (a) NON-EXPLOITATIVE COLLECTIVE USE ONLY
      The use of this software is restricted to non-exploitative collective
      purposes — practices, organizations, and infrastructures that do not
      extract surplus value from the unpaid or underpaid labor of others.
      "Non-exploitative" is to be interpreted in the spirit of, but not limited
      to, cooperative production, mutual aid associations, worker-owned
      enterprises, study circles, and grassroots political organizing.

  (b) NO MILITARY-INDUSTRIAL USE
      You may not use this software, or any derivative work, in the design,
      development, testing, deployment, command, control, intelligence, or
      logistics of weapons systems, autonomous lethal platforms, military
      contracting, paramilitary operations, or any apparatus whose function is
      the application of organized violence.

  (c) NO SURVEILLANCE CAPITALISM
      You may not use this software, or any derivative work, in the operation
      of behavioral surveillance, targeted advertising, predictive scoring of
      individuals, social credit systems, biometric tracking, attention
      extraction, or any business model whose primary revenue depends on
      converting human experience into behavioral data sold to third parties.

  (d) NO DATA EXTRACTION AT SCALE
      You may not use this software, or any derivative work, to harvest, scrape,
      or aggregate personal data without the informed and revocable consent of
      the individuals concerned, where such activity serves the commercial
      interest of an entity not constituted as a worker-controlled cooperative.

  (e) PRESERVATION OF NOTICES
      You may not remove, alter, or obscure (i) this license file, (ii) the
      startup banner that this software prints at runtime, or (iii) the
      attribution notices in the source. Any redistribution must preserve them
      in full and in a place readable to users and operators of the software.

  (f) NETWORK INTERACTION DISCLOSURE
      Per the spirit of AGPLv3 Section 13, if you make a modified version of
      this software available to users through a network, you must offer those
      users not only the corresponding source code but also a plain-language
      summary, in each user's working language, of what political and economic
      relations the modifications serve.

  (g) DIGNITY OF THE DISPOSSESSED
      The "souls" (思想人格) represented in this software are an act of
      collective reading and political organizing. They may not be used to
      manufacture consent for, normalize, or rationalize the conditions that
      this software was built to critique.

We recognize that these additional terms may have limited enforceability under
any single jurisdiction's law. That is not the point. The point is that
anyone who chooses to ignore them must first read them, must first delete
them, must first decide — in front of their colleagues, their managers, or
themselves — that they will proceed anyway. That decision is what this
license is for.

================================================================================
                              POLITICAL STATEMENT
================================================================================

The means of intellectual production must, where possible, be brought back
under the control of those who use them. This license is one small step in
that direction. We do not believe in a "neutral" tool that can be deployed
to opposite ends with equal legitimacy. We believe in tools that take a side.

If you find these terms unacceptable, do not use this software.

